                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1523.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-01T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 1, 1915—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your March 4. Even supposing it has authority of law so to do, which is gravely
                    doubted, Department unwilling authorize transfer money from credit order 1325 to
                    continue work now in progress.</p>
                <p>Department’s policy has been not to interfere with details internal improvements
                    but recognize authority Dominican Congress thereover. Departure from that policy
                    might easily cause serious embarrassment and it is believed should not be made
                    even to avoid suspension public works under way. Responsibility for such
                    suspension apparently rests with Dominican Congress which failed to make
                    appropriation. Moreover, Department understands Congress now in session and of
                    course it may, if it chooses, relieve public works situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
